//CLR implements Dynamic memory for collection classes like stack and queue, so we do not need to worry about the size of the stack or queue when adding or removing elements. The CLR will automatically manage the memory for us and resize the collection as needed. This allows us to focus on using the collection without worrying about memory management.
//intially 2*N size is allocated for stack and when the stack is full, it will double its size to accommodate more elements. This process is known as dynamic resizing and it allows the stack to grow and shrink as needed without the need for manual memory management. The CLR handles this process automatically, ensuring that the stack can efficiently manage its memory while providing a flexible and dynamic collection for storing elements.
